  "prompt": "Do Psychopaths have microexpressions?",
  "response": "Yes, psychopaths can exhibit microexpressions, just like anyone else. Microexpressions are brief, involuntary facial expressions that occur as a result of an emotion someone is experiencing. They usually last only a fraction of a second and can reveal a person's true feelings, even if they are trying to conceal them. Psychopaths may have the ability to control their expressions more effectively than most people, given their typically enhanced social manipulation skills, but microexpressions can still occur and potentially reveal underlying emotions. Detecting these microexpressions often requires careful observation and, sometimes, specialized training.",
